Models.Name: CloudEvent
Models.Description: Properties of an event published to an Azure Messaging EventGrid Namespace topic using the CloudEvent 1.0 Schema.

Properties.Name: id
Properties.Description: An identifier for the event. The combination of id and source must be unique for each distinct event.

Properties.Name: source
Properties.Description: Identifies the context in which an event happened. The combination of id and source must be unique for each distinct event.

Properties.Name: data
Properties.Description: Event data specific to the event type.

Properties.Name: data_base64
Properties.Description: Event data specific to the event type, encoded as a base64 string.

Properties.Name: type
Properties.Description: Type of event related to the originating occurrence.

Properties.Name: time
Properties.Description: The time (in UTC) the event was generated, in RFC3339 format.

Properties.Name: specversion
Properties.Description: The version of the CloudEvents specification which the event uses.

Properties.Name: dataschema
Properties.Description: Identifies the schema that data adheres to.

Properties.Name: datacontenttype
Properties.Description: Content type of data value.

Properties.Name: subject
Properties.Description: This describes the subject of the event in the context of the event producer (identified by source).

Models.Name: PublishResult
Models.Description: The result of the Publish operation.

Models.Name: ReceiveResult
Models.Description: Details of the Receive operation response.

Properties.Name: details
Properties.Description: Array of receive responses, one per cloud event.

ValueType.Name: ReceiveDetails
ValueType.Description: Receive operation details per Cloud Event.

Properties.Name: brokerProperties
Properties.Description: The Event Broker details.

Type.Name: BrokerProperties
Type.Description: Properties of the Event Broker operation.

Properties.Name: lockToken
Properties.Description: The token of the lock on the event.

Properties.Name: deliveryCount
Properties.Description: The attempt count for delivering the event.

Properties.Name: event
Properties.Description: Cloud Event details.

Properties.Name: lockTokens
Properties.Description: Array of lock tokens.

Models.Name: AcknowledgeResult
Models.Description: The result of the Acknowledge operation.

Properties.Name: failedLockTokens
Properties.Description: Array of FailedLockToken for failed cloud events. Each FailedLockToken includes the lock token along with the related error information (namely, the error code and description).

Properties.Name: lockToken
Properties.Description: The lock token of an entry in the request.

Properties.Name: error
Properties.Description: Error information of the failed operation result for the lock token in the request.

Properties.Name: code
Properties.Description: One of a server-defined set of error codes.

Properties.Name: message
Properties.Description: A human-readable representation of the error.

Properties.Name: target
Properties.Description: The target of the error.

Properties.Name: details
Properties.Description: An array of details about specific errors that led to this reported error.

Properties.Name: innererror
Properties.Description: An object containing more specific information than the current object about the error.

Type.Name: InnerError
Type.Description: An object containing more specific information about the error. As per Microsoft One API guidelines - https://github.com/Microsoft/api-guidelines/blob/vNext/Guidelines.md#7102-error-condition-responses.

Properties.Name: code
Properties.Description: One of a server-defined set of error codes.

Properties.Name: innererror
Properties.Description: Inner error.

Properties.Name: succeededLockTokens
Properties.Description: Array of lock tokens for the successfully acknowledged cloud events.

Properties.Name: lockTokens
Properties.Description: Array of lock tokens.

Operations.Name: send
Operations.Description: Publish a single Cloud Event to a namespace topic.

Parameters.Name: endpoint
Parameters.Description: The host name of the namespace, e.g. namespaceName1.westus-1.eventgrid.azure.net

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Operations.Name: sendEvents
Operations.Description: Publish a batch of Cloud Events to a namespace topic.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Parameters.Name: events
Parameters.Description: Array of Cloud Events being published.

Operations.Name: receive
Operations.Description: Receive a batch of Cloud Events from a subscription.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Parameters.Name: maxEvents
Parameters.Description: Max Events count to be received. Minimum value is 1, while maximum value is 100 events. If not specified, the default value is 1.

Parameters.Name: maxWaitTime
Parameters.Description: Max wait time value for receive operation in Seconds. It is the time in seconds that the server approximately waits for the availability of an event and responds to the request. If an event is available, the broker responds immediately to the client. Minimum value is 10 seconds, while maximum value is 120 seconds. If not specified, the default value is 60 seconds.

Operations.Name: acknowledge
Operations.Description: Acknowledge a batch of Cloud Events. The response will include the set of successfully acknowledged lock tokens, along with other failed lock tokens with their corresponding error information. Successfully acknowledged events will no longer be available to be received by any consumer.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Operations.Name: release
Operations.Description: Release a batch of Cloud Events. The response will include the set of successfully released lock tokens, along with other failed lock tokens with their corresponding error information. Successfully released events can be received by consumers.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Parameters.Name: releaseDelayInSeconds
Parameters.Description: Release cloud events with the specified delay in seconds.

Operations.Name: reject
Operations.Description: Reject a batch of Cloud Events. The response will include the set of successfully rejected lock tokens, along with other failed lock tokens with their corresponding error information. Successfully rejected events will be dead-lettered and can no longer be received by a consumer.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.

Operations.Name: renewLocks
Operations.Description: Renew locks for a batch of Cloud Events. The response will include the set of successfully renewed lock tokens, along with other failed lock tokens with their corresponding error information. Successfully renewed locks will ensure that the associated event is only available to the consumer that holds the renewed lock.

Parameters.Name: apiVersion
Parameters.Description: The API version to use for this operation.
